http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/Manisha-Koirala-roped-in-for-Bala%E2%80%99s-Tamil-multi-starrer/article13994059.ece

Actress Manisha Koirala has been brought in for an important role in National Award-winning filmmaker Bala’s next Tamil multi-starrer project.The yet-untitled project is slated to go on the floors starting July.“The film so far features Vishal, Atharvaa, Aarya, Arvind Swamy and Manisha. The makers are also in talks with Anushka Shetty,” a source close to Bala said.The film is rumoured to be titled Kutra Paramparai, and will be produced by Bala’s home banner B Studios.“The project was supposed to go on the floors much earlier. However, due to the delay in the release of Bala’s forthcoming film Tharai Thappattai’, this project was postponed,a the source added.>The Sasi-kumar starrer Tharai Thappattai, the music of which is scored by maestro Ilayaraja, is all set to release worldwide on Thursday.